annotationA: Ceramide kinase (Cerk) catalyzes phosphorylation of ceramide, helping to maintain ceramide levels, which in turn regulates photoreceptor structure and function. Cerk is also a component of WntD signaling and mediates primordial germ cell migration
annotationB: Diacylglycerol binding; diacylglycerol kinase activity; NAD+ kinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: intracellular signal transduction; protein kinase C-activating G-protein coupled receptor signaling pathway; phosphorylation
